719394f-b.title: Manhattan: Dyckman Street - Henshaw Street
719394f-b.text:
(1)
DDyckman Street, north side, from but not including Henshaw
Street, to but not including Staff Street. This is a two story
frage house.
October 26, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPODUCTIONS.
(2)
A more inclusive view eastward.
October 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(3)
A view similar to No. 2. These frame structures have
disappeared today (1933), their sites being included in Inwood Hill
Park with the newly constructed Henry Hudson Parkway traversing same.
01d Bolton Road curved around at the rear of this view and several
the homes shown fronted on same. About 1922 the City took title and
permitted the inhabitants to remain until plans matured, which as
beforeementioned came to a satisfactory conclusion recently. Several
individuals of prominence resided here and the writer believes that Gen.
U.S. Grant's son was one and not necessarily in those shown.
May 1920.
0eorge L. Balgue.
CREDIT LIiE IMPLRATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.
